          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TRt596Y1K884QViLiuUj-123" value="app store or web server that public client came from" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1287.23" y="1331" width="120" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TRt596Y1K884QViLiuUj-124" value="could be from same or different parties. resource server and AS are likely from the same party" style="shape=curlyBracket;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;rounded=1;flipH=1;labelPosition=right;verticalLabelPosition=middle;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;dashed=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1423.23" y="1246" width="67" height="143" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TRt596Y1K884QViLiuUj-125" value="Example&lt;br&gt;SPA could be drawing app and web service could be cloud file storage&amp;nbsp;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1603.23" y="1274" width="174" height="96" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TRt596Y1K884QViLiuUj-126" value="&lt;div&gt;code_verify is high entropy&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;t = transformation method (S256)&lt;/div&gt;code_challenge = t(code_verifier)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;plain transformation method should be avoided and requires encryption&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="587.73" y="1114" width="244.5" height="99" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TRt596Y1K884QViLiuUj-127" value="A malicious program on device&lt;div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;might already have the client ID and secret&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;might be able to read the authz code in the response&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;might be able to read the code_challenge in the request&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The authz code can only be used once. It may be revealed to an attacker after it is received and before it is used by the legitimate requesting client.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;What if a malicious program reads the code_verifier?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The code_verifier can only be used once.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;An attacker cannot use it if the legitimate requester already used it. Since the legitimate requester does not reveal the code_verifier until requesting the authz code, it leaves little time for the attacker to use the code_verifier if stolen.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What if a malicious program reads the access token or refresh token?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;copyshrugemoji__shrug_emoji_text&quot;&gt;¯\_(ツ)_/¯ Original spec assumed that they can be kept secure&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The security of these values varies by platform and device. PKCE is useful mitigation, not a guarantee. It is up to the stakeholders of the device and its software to keep these values secure.&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="207.23000000000002" y="1128.5" width="384" height="386.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TRt596Y1K884QViLiuUj-128" value="client id, client secret, redirect URI, and state not shown here&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;redirect URIs are use a custom scheme/protocol and don&#39;t point to a web server&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="620.23" y="981" width="198.24" height="88" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TRt596Y1K884QViLiuUj-129" value="Instead of giving the AS a redirect URI in step 3, it could already know the redirect URI associated with the given client ID. It is best to register a client&#39;s redirect URI before authz requests and it is required for public clients." style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="508.23" y="768" width="236" height="90" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
